# Language: English code, Dutch UI (resources)

## Code (English only)

- **C#**: identifiers, class/method/property names, file names, namespaces, XML doc comments, inline comments, logs, and `throw` / validation messages in **English**.
- **JavaScript** (e.g. `wwwroot/*.js`): identifiers and comments in **English**; no user-visible Dutch/English literals—surface errors via Blazor/localized strings.
- **API** responses and problem details shown to users must come from localized resources or mapped messages, not hardcoded Dutch in handlers.
- **Exceptions**: seed SQL and recipe content in `scripts/**/*.sql` may stay **Dutch**; `docs/` and `.cursor/rules/` are exempt.

## UI (Dutch via resources)

- All user-visible strings in **Blazor** (labels, buttons, placeholders, `PageTitle`, `aria-label`, status text) use `IStringLocalizer<SharedResources>` (or feature-specific resource classes)—**never** hardcoded Dutch or English in `.razor` markup or `@code` string literals.
- Store Dutch text only in `Resources/SharedResources.nl.resx`. Use **English resource keys** with pattern `[Area].[Element].[Type]` (e.g. `RecipeCreate.Title.Label`, `RecipeCreate.SaveButton`, `Nav.MyRecipes`).
- Default request culture: `nl-NL`. Set `<html lang="nl">` in `App.razor`.
- When adding UI text: add the key to `SharedResources.resx` (neutral fallback), `SharedResources.en-US.resx` (English), and `SharedResources.nl.resx` (Dutch).
- **Language switcher**: show language names in their **native** form (`Nederlands`, `English`) as code constants—not via `L[...]` (so they do not change with UI culture).

## Examples

```razor
@* BAD *@
<label>Ingrediënten</label>

@* GOOD *@
<label>@L["RecipeCreate.Ingredients.SectionLabel"]</label>
```

```csharp
// BAD
throw new ArgumentException("Titel is verplicht.");

// GOOD
throw new ArgumentException("Title is required.");
```

```sql
-- OK in scripts/seed-*.sql
N'Lasagna bestaat uit drie onderdelen...'
```

## Refactors

- Rename Dutch code artifacts to English (e.g. `ReceptenOverzicht` → `RecipeOverview`, `ShowKaartenLabel` → `ShowCardsLabel`).
- Migrate existing inline UI strings to resources before adding new features.
